# i18n & Routing

## URL structure

| Locale | Pattern | Example |
|---|---|---|
| Danish (default) | no prefix | `/kampe`, `/nyheder`, `/hold` |
| English | `/en/` prefix | `/en/kampe`, `/en/nyheder` |

Configured in `astro.config.mjs`: `defaultLocale: 'da'`, `prefixDefaultLocale: false`.

## Adding a page

Mirror both locales when content is user-facing:

```
src/pages/kampe.astro       → Danish
src/pages/en/kampe.astro    → English
```

Static marketing pages can use `export const prerender = true` in both.

## Locale helpers

```ts
import { getLocale, localePath, t, type Locale } from '@/lib/i18n';

const locale = getLocale(Astro.url);           // 'da' | 'en'
const href = localePath('en', '/kampe');       // '/en/kampe'
const label = t[locale].fixtures;              // UI strings
```

Pass `locale` to `<Base locale={locale}>` and Strapi calls (`{ locale }`).

## Middleware

`src/middleware.ts` sets `context.locals.locale` and guards `/konto/profil` routes via Descope cookie `DS`.

## Date formatting

Use locale-aware formatters in page frontmatter:

```ts
date.toLocaleDateString(locale === 'en' ? 'en-GB' : 'da-DK', { ... })
```

Do not hardcode Danish strings in English pages — use `t.en.*` or page-specific English copy.
